entries.s_12: Taibela sent you. I can trust you then. What do you want?
entries.s_14: Faeto isn't looking for you. He's after Untas.
entries.s_16: Thank the Force! I was sure Faeto was after me. What do you want?
entries.s_17: I don't know you and I don't trust you. I only trust my lovely Taibela.
entries.s_20: Prove it. Do you have a token from her for me?
entries.s_22: Well open your back pack and give me what she gave you.
entries.s_23: I told you where to find his pal. Now go.
entries.s_26: Last I heard Sleash and he ran off somewhere. I know that Sleash had some deal in the works with Vaigon Shinn, but I have no clue about Untas. You'll need to convince Sleash to loosen his tongue if you want him to tell you anything.
entries.s_28: And how would I do that?
entries.s_30: This dar' kel spice should do the trick. Go gift it to Sleash before you ask about Untas, and he should tell you anything you want. He has a weakness for this particular spice.
entries.s_46: Huh? I don't have anything to say to you. And tell Faeto to leave me and mine alone.
entries.s_48: I think I'll pass on this one.
entries.s_50: You won't get to him without the dar' kel.
entries.s_9: Go away. I heard what you do. Go!
